   "source": [
    "from scipy.stats import poisson\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "sample_data = np.loadtxt('./Fiesta_Sample.txt', skiprows=2)\n",
    "background_data = np.loadtxt('./Fiesta_Background.txt', skiprows=2)\n",
    "bg_numcount_mean = np.ceil(np.mean(background_data[:,1]))\n",
    "sample_numcounts = sample_data[:,1]-bg_numcount_mean\n",
    "sample_numsamples = sample_data[:,0]\n",
    "min_num = np.min(sample_numcounts)\n",
    "max_num = np.max(sample_numcounts)\n",
    "mu = np.average(sample_numcounts)\n",
    "k = np.arange(min_num, max_num+1)\n",
    "poisson_dist = poisson.pmf(k=k, mu=mu)\n",
    "normal_pdf = norm.pdf(x=k, loc=mu, scale=np.std(sample_numcounts))\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.set_title('Histogram of Radioactive Decay of Sample Data')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Number of Counts', fontsize=16)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=16)\n",
    "ax.plot(k,poisson_dist)\n",
    "ax.plot(k, normal_pdf)\n",
    "ax.hist(sample_numcounts, bins=100, density=True)\n",
    "ax.legend(['Poisson Distribution', 'Normal Distribution'])"
   ],
